===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} ''[[scip]]'', from {{proto|Germanic|skipam}} (compare West Frisian {{term|skip|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|schip|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Schiff|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|skib|lang=da}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|skēi-b-||ski-b-}} (compare Lithuanian {{term|skiebti|skiẽbti|lang=lt}} ‘to rip up’, Latvian {{term|skibit|škibît|lang=lv}} ‘to cut, lop’).

